What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Functional Apparel Market?



Market Analysis and Size

The world's leading textile engineers and designers work to produce high-quality functional garments, and significant investments take place in the growth of innovative and new technologies and products in the sports, military sectors and others. Functional apparel provides the wearer good comfort because it has excellent moisture-wicking properties, which enable sweat to transfer from the inside to the outside of the cloth. Furthermore, these products are used in the sports and military sector and are now employed in the manufacture of casual and urban clothing.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the functional apparel market was valued at USD 360.00 billion in 2021 and is expected to reach USD 797.31 billion by 2029, registering a CAGR of 10.45% during the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.



